### Create action using curl
POST http://localhost:3000/api/action
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "curl",
  "content": "curl http://localhost:3000/api/dummy",
  "actionName": "accountUpgrade",
  "description": "upgrade the account"
}

### Create action using OpenAPI spec (YAML)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/action
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "openapi",
  "content": "openapi: 3.0.3\ninfo:\n  title: Sample API\n  version: 1.0.0\npaths:\n  /example:\n    get:\n      summary: Example endpoint\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Success",
  "actionName": "sampleApiYaml",
  "description": "Sample OpenAPI specification"
}

### Create action using OpenAPI spec (JSON)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/action
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "openapi",
  "content": "{\"openapi\": \"3.0.3\", \"info\": {\"title\": \"Sample API\", \"version\": \"1.0.0\"}, \"paths\": {\"/example\": {\"get\": {\"summary\": \"Example endpoint\", \"responses\": {\"200\": {\"description\": \"Success\"}}}}}}",
  "actionName": "sampleApiJson",
  "description": "Sample OpenAPI specification in JSON"
}

### Get action by name
GET http://localhost:3000/api/action/accountUpgrade
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json


